data: Jack believes he can make big money by looking for uranium in the desert. After stopping at a camping supply store (where Frank Nelson works), Jack, Mary, and Rochester head into the desert and set up camp. Later, Jack overhears a group of men talking about digging nearby the next day; believing they're also uranium hunters, Jack gets up early the next morning and start digging in the spot they were talking about. He digs a six-foot-deep hole before he discovers that they're just repairing a gas pipeline.

Jack blames his nasty cold on Don Wilson, and wants to fire him. He tells the story in a flashback: Don had invited Jack and the gang to his house for dinner but, despite Jack's repeated advice, didn't call his wife to let her know about it. Once they were at Don's house, Don decided to tell his wife that some people from work might drop by, and then have the others "arrive" one at a time. Jack was the last one left, and he was detained by a burglar in the rain (during which they did the famous "Your money or your life" routine). In the present, Jack decides not to fire Don because Jack feels guilty about how little he's paying him.

table-1065-589.caption: Works in Cathedrals and Parish Churches
data: Subject of Woore's window in the church's South Aisle is the 104th Psalm.
A two-light window in the South Aisle West area of All Saints is in memory of L and R.Roberts. The theme is "Suffer little Children".

G.F.Bodley designed this church and work began on the Chancel in 1903, though a lack of funds was to delay completion. The church was finally consecrated on 1 February 1915. Woore's first window in this church is called "Endurance through Sacrifice" and was installed in 1919 as a gift from Mrs Percy Watson, a thanksgiving for the safe return from the Great War of her three sons, Percy, John and Robert. The 1920 window entitled "The Marriage at Cana" is a memorial to Grace Mary Walter (1890–1918). The subject is Jesus turning water into wine (John 2:1). J.Ballantine added glass to the tracery of "The Marriage at Cana" in 1929.
The four-light window at the Eastern end of the South Aisle was a work by Woore whilst at Whall and Whall.
Woore designed a window for the South Chancel. Image shown above appears courtesy Tina Negus.
Woore completed a four-light window in the South Chapel area.
Woore's window in the North Aisle West area is of two-lights and has depictions of the Saints Osmund and Bede in the South side and Alban and Edward in the North side.
Church of St James and St Basil

Woore did some of his best work for this church. Sadly the church is now closed and it is understood that the building has been sold. This church also contained stained glass by Wilhelmina Geddes, Edward Burne-Jones, William Alkman, Percy Bacon, John Houghton Bonner, Henry Gustav Hiller and Gilbert P Gamon. The Woore window is signed "The Artificers' Guild".
St Mary's two-light West window is by Woore and has a pattern of flowers on clear glass.
Woore completed a two-light window for the old church

The East window in St Andrew's is a three-light window which depicts "The Good Shepherd". The inscription reads "I am the good shepherd I know my sheep and am known as mine". The central light portrays the Good Shepherd, the left hand light shows St Andrew and that on the left St Peter. Whilst Woore designed the main window, Carl Edwards designed the tracery glass in 1962 which shows symbols of the Passion.

Woore's window for this church depicts the Sower and the Harvester. The window is in memory of Charles Bass, a previous vicar of the church. The inscription reads "I am come that they might have life and that they might have it more abundantly." John 10:10. The window is of two-lights and located in the South Aisle South East.

Woore complete a window for this church in 1921. It is called the "St George" window and is in memory of Lt Arthur Frederick Evans of the 100th Squadron of the RAF, who was killed in action on 30 October 1918 at Langres in France. Woore was also responsible for the "Leyland" window which is inscribed "In memory of John & Elizabeth Leyland and their son John, Churchwarden 1923–1934 and superintendent of Prescot Parish Church Sunday School 1918–1934". Another Woore window in this church includes a depiction of Jesus stood in a boat on the sea of Galilee in the upper section and in the lower section, 'The Sower', a man is shown sowing seeds and oxen pulling a plough, this window also dating to 1938. In the top 3 panels of the "Leyland" window we see Jesus in the temple with his disciples and young children with their mothers. They had brought their infants to him so he might touch them. The disciples rebuked the mothers for doing so, but Jesus was much displeased and said to them "Suffer little children to come unto me and forbid them not, for such is the Kingdom of God ". Mark 10 v.13-14. The bottom part of the window shows St Andrew, St Christopher and St Elizabeth of Hungary.
Woore's circular East window, with three divisions, depicts Christ the Shepherd flanked by a Nativity scene and an angel with chalice.
St Peter's and St Paul's Church

This church was badly damaged by German bombs in 1941 but had been rebuilt by 1957. Woore designed windows for the North wall of the Children's Chapel these showing scenes from the childhood of Jesus. The Western and Central windows are memorials to the Beer family and are inscribed "in loving memory of Norah Gregory Beer and her three children, Douglas, Rosemary & Graham." These portray the "Flight into Egypt" and "The Adoration of the Magi".

Woore's window in the North Choir area is in memory of William Pare Roberts, Dean of Salisbury 1907–19 and his wife Margaret Grace Pare Roberts. The window is of two-lights and depicts scenes from Ruth in one light and scenes from David in another.
This is now a Polish church and was previously St John's. Has a five-light "Christ in Majesty" East window.
Woore made the Coat of Arms in a stained glass window to commemorate the coronation of Elizabeth II. The window is in the South Porch.

In the four panels of Woore's window in this church, which represents the Annunciation, the first shows an angel with harp, the second an angel, thought to be Gabriel, the third shows Mary and the fourth an angel with a stringed instrument similar to a violin/viola. This information courtesy Kay Rothwell at St Mary's. The window is the East window.
For this Whalley church, Woore executed a two-light window with the figures of St Anthony and St Giles.
There is a four-light window in the South Chapel by Woore.
St Philip church was absorbed into that at Christ Church and St Philip's Church itself was demolished. There were Woore windows in the Chapel of St Philip's.
The Church of St John the Baptist
This Church built 1915–16 had a Woore window (the East window in the South wall). The church was converted into flats in 1986/87.
For the East Chantry area, Woore executed a four-light window which depicts Henry III, Edward III, Henry V and Henry VII. .
The second window in the South Aisle is by Woore. It is of two-lights and depicts a nurse and soldier in one light and the Madonna and child in the second.
West window is of three-lights and in memory of the Rev.Augustus Gibson. The window depicts the Sower, Suffer little children and the Reaper.

table-1065-282.caption: Listed buildings
data: The remains of a two storey merchant's house of upper hall-house type, which may have been used as a counting-house. Little now remains other than the exterior walls. Scheduled as an ancient monument.

Remains of a merchant's house which originally stood on the quayside. The west wall was incorporated in the city defences after the French raid of 1338. This house is one of the most complete of the larger 12th century town houses surviving in the country. Scheduled as an ancient monument. The building is misnamed as historians originally believed that King John stayed in the building in the early 1300s.
Merchant's house with shop with galleried interior. Also known as 58 French Street, this is claimed to be the earliest complete mediaeval house surviving in England. Scheduled as an ancient monument.

This was the chapel of the Hospital of St. Julien or God's House which was founded circa 1185 as an almshouse and hostel for travellers on pilgrimage to Canterbury. It was used regularly by French Protestants from the 16th century until 1939 and is thus also known as the French Church.

The oldest building still in use in the city and the only church still active of the five originally in the medieval walled town. Underneath the church in the north-west corner is a late mediaeval vault which is a scheduled ancient monument.
Section of wall running west from Polymond Tower to remains of semi-circular tower to east of Bargate. The wall is scheduled as an ancient monument.

Section of wall running west from Bargate to Arundel Tower and then south to point just south of Castle Water Gate. It includes Arundel Tower, Catchcold Tower, Garderobe Tower, The 40 Steps, Castle Water Gate and Castle Vault. Scheduled as an ancient monument.
Section of wall running north from God's House along back of the Walls to Round Tower, incorporating a 13th-century half drum tower. Scheduled as an ancient monument.

Sections of Mediaeval City Wall running south along Western Esplanade from south-west corner of Simnel Street to University Air Squadron Headquarters at south end of Bugle Street. Includes The Arcades, The West Gate, Blue Anchor Postern and Biddles Gate. Scheduled as an ancient monument.

Late Mediaeval town house, built in its present form mainly by Sir John Dawtrey at some time between 1491 and 1518, but incorporating a banqueting hall built a hundred years earlier. Now open to the public as the "Tudor House Museum". Scheduled as an ancient monument.

This was built, after the French raid of 1338, by Cistercian Monks as a storehouse for wool to be exported to Europe. It is the only surviving freestanding mediaeval warehouse in Southampton. Scheduled as an ancient monument. Until 2011, this was the home of the Southampton Maritime Museum.

"Bugle House", formerly "The Vicarage", is built of yellow brick and has three storeys, attics and a basement. At the top it has a three light semi-circular window to attic storey. The porch has Doric columns and pilasters with a frieze with Greek key pattern and moulded cornice. The interior has a contemporary curved staircase with cast iron balusters, cornices and good door surrounds with female masks in the corners. It is now occupied by the Southampton & Fareham Chamber of Commerce.

Chapel Mills was the third steam mill constructed in England, but is today the last early generation steam mill of its kind in the country. It supplied the Royal Navy with ships' biscuits during the American War of Independence and the Napoleonic Wars. Today, with the steam mill, bakehouse and grain store still intact, it is the last example standing. It is currently being converted into housing and office units.

Remains of the drum towers flanking the principal gateway to Southampton's Mediaeval Castle. These twin drum towers were added to the defensive bailey wall of the Royal Castle. Stone rubble walls to a height of nearly 20 ft with several arches, some now blocked. Scheduled as an ancient monument.

This former coaching inn was built in the late 18th century. The lower three storeys are probably pre-1800 with the fourth storey added in the 1830s. The roof is concealed by a ball moulded balustrade at roof level with central Royal Arms in colour. The inscription to left of central arch on a stone reads "Coach to London (Sundays excepted) Alresford, Alton performs 10 hours".

Now known as Westgate Hall. Built before 1428, this building originally stood in St Michael's Square. The upper floors were used as the town Woollen Cloth Hall and the open arcaded ground floor as the Fishmarket. By the 17th century it had become derelict and was sold for re-erection on the present site as a warehouse, at which time the arcaded ground floor was filled in. Now available for hire as a venue for civil marriages, wedding receptions, private parties, concerts, lectures, meetings and conferences.

table-1065-879.caption: Season 1 (2012)
data: Quinn Perkins comes to what she believes to be a blind date, only to find that she is now getting offered a job at Pope & Associates, a job that she's dreamed about for a while; Olivia Pope and Stephen work on getting a Russian Ambassadors baby back from kidnappers. Just as they are all about to leave Lieutenant Sully St. James comes in pleading for help as his girlfriend had just been murdered; Olivia gets a call from Cyrus as a woman named Amanda Tanner has been saying she has been sleeping with the president and request her help. After Olivia talks to, or so threatens, Amanda, Quinn questions if she wants the job. Olivia goes to David Rossen asking for 36 hours as so they can clear Sully's name; As the clock ticks Abby and Stephen look for concrete evidence for Sully's alibi, finding a security camera with Sully kissing another man. Sully refuses to admit that he is gay, as he's a open anti-gay republican; Quinn convinces Olivia that Amanda isn't lying as the president called her 'Sweet Baby', the same name he used for Olivia. Olivia convinces Sully to come out as gay, and then takes Amanda in as her new client.

Pope & Associates' new client is one of the biggest madams in all of D.C., finding that she is about to go to jail for the rest of her life; Olivia finds that Cyrus took away her access to the White House. Olivia sets Quinn up to look after Amanda, only to find that she walked away from the hospital; Abby finds herself jealous when she sees that Stephen was on the list of people that slept with one of the madam's call-girls. Olivia goes to Amanda only to find that Amanda doesn't want anything to do with her; Quinn meets a reporter named Gideon and finds that he is looking to make a story out of Amanda trying to kill herself. One of the names on the 'client list' is Fitzs' candidate to be on the Supreme Court, but when they question him they find that he doesn't know anything about it; Olivia finds that it is his wife that he slept with years ago and convinces her to tell him that she was a call girl. Fitz gives back Olivia's access to the White House; While Amanda comes to Olivia saying that she wants help. Gideon finds that he has a story; As the madame is put out of business and her clients are never revealed to the public if they endorse President Grant's candidate, per Olivia's orders.

Pope & Associates' current client is a man who is being charged with rape, even though the stories don't add up; Mellie begins to worry about Fitz when she finds that he isn't sleeping anymore. Amanda moves in with Olivia and request that she have a meeting with the President; While investigating the 'rape' Harrison finds that the defendants' best friend was raped by their client, and that she was framing him for rape. Mellie invites Olivia to the Presidential Ball, finding that he'll be able to sleep now; Quinn starts flirting with Gideon in an effort to find out the information that he knows on Amanda. After talking to her client, Olivia convinces her to turn her son into the police, even though the woman he raped is already dead; Cyrus talks Olivia out of meeting with the president at 'their spot'; Fitz finds that Mellie knew about his affair with Olivia the entire time. Even with Olivia canceling the meeting, Amanda request that the meeting be put back on; Cyrus finds that someone recorded Fitz and Amanda having sex. Amanda confesses to Olivia that she's pregnant with the Presidents' child.

A South American dictator comes to Pope & Associates when he finds out that his family has been kidnapped; Cyrus begins digging into everyone in Pope & Associate's backgrounds. Olivia finds that her world is upside down when Amanda's pregnancy test come out to be true; Quinn begins going on dates with Gideon, but is skeptical to the fact that he says that he doesn't need her as a source anymore because he has someone else. Abby and Harrison find that General Flores's wife didn't really get kidnapped, that she attempted to leave him, but when Abby takes it into her own hands to help her, Olivia returns them back to the General, causing Abby and Olivia to get into a fight. Gideon begins researching everything about Amanda Tanner and the President; While Fitz begins wondering what would happened if everything came out into the public. Olivia helps the Generals wife leave her husband, and eventually convince him to let her take the children. In the middle of the night Amanda Tanner is kidnapped from Olivia's house, while she and the rest of the 'Gladiators' prepare for the trial; Cyrus and Olivia come to blows and decide that it is now a full blown 'war'.

Abby and Harrison find that General Flores's wife didn't really get kidnapped, that she attempted to leave him, but when Abby takes it into her own hands to help her, Olivia returns them back to the General, causing Abby and Olivia to get into a fight. Gideon begins researching everything about Amanda Tanner and the President; While Fitz begins wondering what would happened if everything came out into the public. Olivia helps the Generals wife leave her husband, and eventually convince him to let her take the children. In the middle of the night Amanda Tanner is kidnapped from Olivia's house, while she and the rest of the 'Gladiators' prepare for the trial; Cyrus and Olivia come to blows and decide that it is now a full blown 'war'.

With Amanda Tanner missing, everyone at Pope & Associates are looking for clues to find her, that is until they get a call that a plane crashed in the woods of Virginia. Olivia works to find the truth about what truly happened, as the pilot had been accused of drinking the night before the plane crashed; Huck gets in touch with someone that he knew before he began working for Olivia, because he found footage linking him to the kidnapping of Amanda. Olivia then asks Huck to go back and do what he knew how to do best; Harrison and Abby find that one of the reports from the plane was copied, meaning that there was something wrong with the plane. Stephen finds it hard to find information out the same way he used to now that he is engaged; President Fitz begins to try to pass an act called the 'Dream Act', and the vote comes down to Vice President Sally Langston, who eventually agrees to pass it. Huck finds out where Amanda's body is, and they go in search to find it; Fitz gets angry when he finds he can't leave the white house. Stephen finds that Amanda's baby wasn't the Presidents, and Fitz shows up at Olivia apartment.

data: Secretary of Defense Curry arrives at Sainte Marine to negotiate with Chaplin and Kendal. Meanwhile, part of the sonar array protecting the island fails, allowing vessels to approach undetected. Lieutenant Shepard is forced to pilot the submarine to repair the array with King and Girard's help. When navy subs have a chance to sink the Colorado, Admiral Shepard shoots Curry and kills his adviser to prevent the firing order. In Washington, Sinclair finds herself cornered and seeks the alliance of Kendals's wife, Christine, to help her uncover the government conspiracy.

Chaplin investigates his crew to find out who sabotaged the sub and stole his launch key, increasing tensions. Conflict is also renewed with Serrat, the local organized crime leader, as he assisted in the BZ attack, and also because his men have been dealing drugs to the crew, with serious consequences for Prosser. Meanwhile, the surviving SEAL from the BZ attack tells Kendal that there is a faction in Washington that wants to see the Colorado crew become a symbol of resistance against the current administration, with a promise of amnesty for the crew, but only if Chaplin is removed from command. Back in the U.S., Christine Kendal and Sinclair work together to expose the truth of what is happening to the Colorado in the national media.

A battle of alliances ensues as Chaplin receives news from Admiral Shepard about the planned coup in the U.S. Still reeling from the belief that his wife is dead, Kendal is torn between his loyalty to Chaplin, a growing concern with the Chinese intentions, fear that the coup d'etat is not the way to move forward. Prosser's mutiny team covertly sinks a Chinese supply ship as it approaches shore. It is revealed that Chaplin has a man, Brannan, inside Prosser's mutiny team. The Speaker announces to the House that he had been planning to join the coup, followed seconds later by his suicide and the uncovering of most of the conspirators. Sinclair learns that her father is supporting the President in his treachery, and he protects her from being named a conspirator in exchange for her joining the President's efforts.

Sinclair plays along with her father and the President, showing her loyalty by killing her lover, while she arranges for Kendall's wife to be returned to the US. She then reveals the proof of the President's treachery before assassinating him.

title: Objectivity
Subjectivity
table-1065-12.pgTitle: Concluding Unscientific Postscript to Philosophical Fragments
table-1065-12.caption: Contrasts in
data: Objective truth is that which relates to propositions, that which has no relation to the existence of the knower. History, science, and speculative philosophy all deal with objective knowledge. According to Climacus, all objective knowledge is subject to doubt. Focuses on what is asserted.

Subjective truth is essential or ethico-religious truth. It is not composed of propositions or perceptions of the external world, but of introspection, experiences, and especially one's relationship with God.

Direct Communication consists of statements that can be communicated and understood without appropriation, that is, without experiencing personally what is being communicated. Objective knowledge can be communicated directly.
Indirect Communication requires appropriation on the part of the receiver. The receiver must experience or have experienced what is being communicated, not just hear it.

data: As an angry mob gathers outside the precinct, Stonebridge comes across the lone police officer there. When reinforcements arrive, Stonebridge realises that it is Kohl and a partner in disguise. Stonebridge kills them, but in retaliation, Matlock attacks the precinct, kills the shooter and captures Stonebridge. Meanwhile at a hospital, two doctors are revealed to be assassins and finish off Lutulu. After Scott and Lilian escape Hanson's team, Matlock calls Scott for a trade; Stonebridge for Lilian. Realising that Knox is involved with her father's death, she agrees to it. At Knox's camp, she reads her father's journal that mentions Knox has nuclear weapons. She secretly meets with Scott to reveal Knox's location. As they assault the camp, Lilian shafts Knox in the press. Knox escapes, however Scott and Stonebridge intercept one of the nuclear weapons.

David learns the truth about the Cytron case; Olivia, Cyrus, Mellie, Hollis and Verna go to extremes to protect themselves. Verna tells Fitz she was the one who tried to assassinate him. She also reveals to him the plan to rig the election in his favor. Fitz removes Verna's oxygen mask and holds her hands back, that ultimately kills her. At her funeral, Fitz gives the eulogy and makes no mention of a bad Verna. Fitz also calls off the divorce after Oliva turns down Edison's proposal so she can wait for Fitz's divorce to be final. Fitz then seems angry at Olivia.

table-1065-886.caption: Episodic Synopsis
data: In the late 1960s, four families live in three houses along a narrow bustling street on North Bridge Road. Lin Xiaobei is the only son of a tailor. He fights and gets himself into countless trouble, and is a constant annoyance to his neighbours. Yao Jianhong, who grows up with Xiaobei, is the only person who could tame him. From young, Jianhong and her father perform martial arts in the streets to sell medicated ointment. She is in the ‘turf' for years, and is a candid and forthright girl with a sense of chivalry. Besides Xiaobei and Jianhong, their other childhood friends include Huang Zhihao (nicknamed Tarzan), who loves to day-dream; Tarzan's younger sister Huang Jinhao, who cares about her looks more than anything; the sickly but intelligent Qin Huimin; and the timid Yao Wuji... Xiaobei loves novelty. One day, he takes Huimin and Jinhao to the Shui Xian Men shopping area to show off his findings – fake eyelashes – the latest product from England. Jinhao becomes obsessed and she spends $4 on renting a pair. Jianhong's father Yao Shi is a habitual gambler. He organises a gambling session and mama-san Lucy joins in. Halfway through the game, Lucy sneaks into the room next door to fool around with Hui Min's father, “Uncle Handsome” Qin Xianglin. One of the gamblers tries to get fresh with Jianhong, so Jianhong teaches him a lesson. Tarzan is obsessed with car-racing, yet he cannot drive as he failed the Highway Code test eight times. He vows to pass his ninth attempt, and he asks Jianhong, whom he likes, for a movie date after he pass. Egg prices plummet drastically, so He Jiao, a miser, eats eggs for every meal. Being extremely suspicious by nature, He Jiao thinks Jianhong stole two eggs from her and she confronts Jianhong. Jinhao puts on her fake eyelashes, but no one notices any difference in her. When Jinhao drops one of the eyelashes and Jianhong steps on it by accident, Jinhao demands that Jianhong compensates her. Jianhong refuses. Wuji runs a comic book stall, but he frequently gets too engrossed reading them and forget to collect payment. Xiaobei often passes his time by reading at the stall, and Jianhong is displeased he wastes his time away frivolously. Gangster Big Black Mole takes liberties with Jianhong when he comes to collect protection money. Xiaobei confronts him but Jianhong stops Xiaobei. Xiaobei asks Tarzan to help him take revenge on Big Black Mole...

Tarzan is taking his theory test for the ninth time. Xiaobei tries to help by dressing Tarzan up to look like someone important, but Tarzan fails again. He locks himself in his room in shame, and Jinhao is shocked. Jianhong performs some beautiful sword moves to help Yao Shi sell medicated ointment. Big Black Mole shows up, and he threatens Jianhong to go on a movie date with him, or he will stir trouble. Xiaobei reads the newspapers while selling clothes at a night market. Inspired by what he reads, Xiaobei dreams of travelling around the world by plane someday. Jinhao pesters Xiaobei into buying her some underwear. Jianhong and Wuji arrive, and Jianhong confronts Jinhao for taking $10 from the comic book stall. Jinhao claims it is compensation for her fake eyelashes and the ladies fight. Xiaobei promises to help Jinhao repay Jianhong, so Jinhao is elated. Jinhao spites Jianhong with the gift from Xiaobei. Jianhong gets angry with Xiaobei, so she leaves. Jinhao insults Wuji for complaining to Jianhong. While brewing medicine in the kitchen, Lin Yi asks Huimin to help him with a letter in English. It turns out to be a notification for Xiaobei to report for national service. As Xiaobei is Lin Yi's only son, Lin Yi gets worried. Distracted, Lin Yi causes a fire. Jianhong, Tarzan and Xiaobei put the fire out. Landlord couple He Jiao and Huang Lifa have long wanted to get rid of these tenants so they can sell their house. They use this as an excuse to demand compensation from Lin Yi or move out. As Xiaobei scorches his arm, Jianhong gives Xiaobei some medical pills that Yao Shi kept as treasure. Yao Shi feels heartache. Huimin faints from low blood pressure, so her mother Liu Maomao rushes out to buy her some pig's liver soup. Xianglin seizes the chance to search where Maomao hides her money. He complains to Huimin that Maomao holds the purse strings so tightly that he has no money for vanishing cream or hair wax, so Huimin shows him the ladies' earrings she found on the bed. Xianglin cowers out. Xianglin calls out for Lucy in his sleep, so Maomao hits him. Jinhao mocks at Wuji for being a sissy again. When Wuji discovers a fist-fighting manual that Yao Shi compiled, he tries to learn from it on his own, hoping it will make him more macho. Maomao confronts Lucy and they quarrel on the streets..

Maomao and Lucy fights. One a former female gangster nicknamed “Scarlet Butterfly”, and another, a shrew from working many years as a lady of pleasure, both of them end up being injured. When everyone is watching the fight, Xiaobei and Tarzan steal some sodas and eggs from the coffee shop, with the intention of selling them at a grand car-racing event. Jianhong discovers, so Xiaobei drags her along. While Tarzan watches the race enthusiastically, Xiaobei and Jianhong busy themselves selling the items. Big Black Mole discovers it was Xiaobei and Tarzan who attacked him, so he followed them to the race. The three youngsters manage to thwart his advances with wit. Because of Big Black Mole, Xiaobei makes a loss on the ‘venture', and Tarzan gets a beating from Lifa. Jianhong wants to help Tarzan with her savings, but discovers Yao Shi gambled it away. As Xianglin is afraid Maomao will pursue his affair with Lucy, he pretends to have a brain concussion. Maomao is so worried she seeks help from the temples. Huimin confronts her father, yet Xianglin blames Maomao. Wuji agrees to help Jinhao clean a chamber pot. When Yao Shi discovers, he punishes Wuji to half-squat outside his room. Jinhao lures Xiaobei to her room, and Xiaobei gets a shock when Jinhao changes into a sexy negligee. Jinhao explains she wishes to enter a “Queen of Beds” contest, so she needs Xiaobei to take some photographs of her for the entry. Xiaobei eventually agrees. As He Jiao returns unexpectedly, Jinhao hides Xiaobei. When Jinhao finds a chance to let Xiaobei escape, Wuji misunderstands their relationship. Xiaobei spots Big Black Mole leading his men to the comic book stall. He grabs a piece of rock and follow behind Big Black Mole, but another young man at the stall subdues Big Black Mole before Xiaobei can take action. The young man reveals his police identity.

Because of Big Black Mole, Xiaobei makes a loss on the ‘venture', and Tarzan gets a beating from Lifa. Jianhong wants to help Tarzan with her savings, but discovers Yao Shi gambled it away. As Xianglin is afraid Maomao will pursue his affair with Lucy, he pretends to have a brain concussion. Maomao is so worried she seeks help from the temples. Huimin confronts her father, yet Xianglin blames Maomao. Wuji agrees to help Jinhao clean a chamber pot. When Yao Shi discovers, he punishes Wuji to half-squat outside his room. Jinhao lures Xiaobei to her room, and Xiaobei gets a shock when Jinhao changes into a sexy negligee. Jinhao explains she wishes to enter a “Queen of Beds” contest, so she needs Xiaobei to take some photographs of her for the entry. Xiaobei eventually agrees. As He Jiao returns unexpectedly, Jinhao hides Xiaobei. When Jinhao finds a chance to let Xiaobei escape, Wuji misunderstands their relationship. Xiaobei spots Big Black Mole leading his men to the comic book stall. He grabs a piece of rock and follow behind Big Black Mole, but another young man at the stall subdues Big Black Mole before Xiaobei can take action. The young man reveals his police identity.

The young policeman is De Hua, Jian Hong's cousin. De Hua gives “Big Black Mole” a warning, but on seeing Xiao Bei is holding a rock, he wants to search Xiao Bei as well. Xiao Bei retaliates, so Jian Hong helps explain. Xiao Bei gets jealous on seeing Jian Hong and De Hua seem close. He uses some harsh words on Jian Hong, so Jian Hong steps on his feet as revenge. Wu Ji misunderstands Xiao Bei took advantage of Jin Hao, so he tries to hit Xiao Bei with the new strokes he learnt. Xiao Bei gives in to Wu Ji, but retaliates when Wu Ji shows no sign of stopping. Later when Wu Ji discovers why Xiao Bei was in Jin Hao's room, the two young men reconcile. He Jiao eavesdrops on Mao Mao and family, but Mao Mao discovers and the two women quarrel. Mao Mao knows He Jiao is trying to evict her tenants, so she tells He Jiao she can drop the idea. That night, Wu Ji awakes from a nightmare about serving the national service, but he gets a bigger shock when he spots a dark shadow on his way to the toilet. Believing the old building is haunted, Jin Hao is afraid to go to the toilet alone. She asks Xiao Bei to accompany her, and she kisses him as gratitude. Hui Min has always been sickly, so getting to school each morning becomes a chore. Xiao Bei decides to takes her to school on his bicycle, but her school friends teases Hui Min by saying Xiao Bei is her boyfriend. Hui Min is embarrassed, so Xiao Bei claims Hui Min is his younger sister. Xiao Bei learns from Wu Ji that Jian Hong is going out with ‘cousin' De Hua, and that Yao Shi intends to matchmake Jian Hong and De Hua. When De Hua arrives in a brand new motorcycle, Xiao Bei and Tarzan decide to join hands in dealing against De Hua…

Xiao Bei and Tarzan shove some bananas into the exhaust pipe of De Hua's motorcycle, so De Hua is embarrassed when it wouldn't start. Xiao Bei and Tarzan are secretly pleased, yet Yao Shi discovers their trick. Yao Shi removes the blockage so De Hua can leave with Jian Hong, and he lectures Xiao Bei and Tarzan for not playing fair. Xiao Bei keeps imagining that Jian Hong and De Hua must be getting intimate. He bumps into a crippled man with a paper bag, and he later discovers the bag behind an altar. On realising the bag contains a batch of gold items, Xiao Bei puts it back. Just then, some detectives show up and question Xiao Bei if he knows where the crippled man is. Xiao Bei denies. On returning to the tailor shop, Xiao Bei decides to retrieve and keep the bag of gold. He returns for the paper bag, but Jian Hong followed him there and stops him. When the crippled man returns for the bag, he gets shot to death by ambushing police. Xiao Bei is glad he listened to Jian Hong's advice. Jian Hong tells Xiao Bei she went out with De Hua to visit her sick aunt, so Xiao Bei rests his mind. Yao Shi is out busy gambling, so Xiao Bei volunteers to help Jian Hong sell medicated ointment. As Xiao Bei is a good talker, the ointments sell out rapidly. Jian Hong shoves Xiao Bei some money and insists he keeps it. When Xiao Bei discovers Jian Hong pawned her gold necklaces to raise money for Xiao Bei to clear his debts, Xiao Bei is touched. He Jiao decides to work on evicting Xiang Lin's family first. On seeing Hui Min is always sickly, He Jiao asks Li Fa to scare Hui Min by pretending to be a ghost. To Li Fa's surprise, Hui Min is not at all afraid and she grabs Li Fa. Li Fa breaks free and he escape, but Xiao Bei tails him. Xiao Bei wants Li Fa to offset his debt or he will expose him …

Jian Hong advises Wu Ji to look for a job, but Wu Ji refuses as he feels contented now. Xiao Bei drags Wu Ji along to the beauty contest to support Jin Hao, and Wu Ji feels shy seeing her in revealingly sleepwear. Despite her good performance, Jin Hao fails to get a placing. Xiao Bei learns that the result has been fixed, so he decides to help her claim justice. The owner of the mattress company tries to get into Jin Hao's pants. Xiao Bei and Wu Ji threaten to expose the guy in the newspaper, so the guy pays them off. When Jian Hong finds out, she blames Xiao Bei for leading Wu Ji astray. Xiao Bei defends himself, but Jian Hong retorts that both Xiao Bei and Jin Hao are shameless. On hearing this, Jin Hao dashes out from Xiao Bei's room in anger, so Jian Hong is mistaken they are having an affair. Jian Hong refuses to listen to Xiao Bei's explanation. As Tarzan misunderstands that Xiao Bei bullied Jian Hong, he punches Xiao Bei before clarifying. Li Fa and He Jiao pay a property agent to help evict their tenants, not knowing the agent is in cahoots with Xiang Lin. Xiang Lin uses the money to compensate Lucy, but she refuses to settle. The cinema is screening a Japanese erotica film, causing a stir. Xiao Bei sees a business opportunity...

Xiao Bei and Jin Hao partner in touting tickets for the Japanese erotica film. Xiang Lin takes Mao Mao to the movie, and Mao Mao is embarrassed as they run into many people they know, including Lucy's god brother, plainclothes police Inspector Yang. Inspector Yang hints he will be teaching Mao Mao a lesson. The police raids Mao Mao's fruits shop. Xiao Bei alerts Hui Min to escape with the gambling bets, but De Hua finds Hui Min. Jian Hong persuades De Hua to let Hui Min off. Mao Mao decides to apologise to Lucy, but Lucy demands an expensive apology feast. Mao Mao agrees reluctantly. As Yao Shi chalks up a huge gambling debt, Lucy suggests he let Jian Hong work as a dance hostess. When Jian Hong learns about the amount he owes, she is shocked. Tarzan and Xiao Bei confirm with Jian Hong she is going to be a dance hostess, but they do not believe that she is doing it out of greed for money. They confront Yao Shi, who admits Jian Hong is helping him repay his debts. Yao Shi asks Xiao Bei if he will look down on Jian Hong. Though Xiao Bei replies no, Yao Shi says he will never let Jian Hong marry a good-for-nothing like him. Wu Ji refuses to report for national service as he heard he needs to strip naked for the medical check. Jian Hong fails to change his mind, but Xiao Bei convinces Wu Ji. Xiao Bei tells Jian Hong he understands why she made that choice. When Wu Ji learns that Jian Hong is going to become a dance hostess, he feels ashamed he fails to shoulder that responsibility…

Wu Ji approaches “Big Black Mole”, who suggests that Wu Ji works as a transvestite on Bugis Street. Wu Ji accepts, and he practises walking with high heels shoes. When Jin Hao walks in on him, Wu Ji confides in her. It breaks Xiao Bei and Tarzan's heart when Lucy teaches Jian Hong how to dance, yet Jian Hong has trouble trying to dance alluringly. Xiao Bei tries to help Jian Hong. He asks Jin Hao to chip in for the capital to sell a batch of fashionable new bras. To help with the business, Jin Hao volunteers to model for Xiao Bei, so he can take some product photographs. When Jin Hao learns that Xiao Bei is raising money for Jian Hong, Jin Hao asks Xiao Bei if he would do the same for her. Jin Hao is elated Xiao Bei says yes. He Jiao returns. Xiao Bei and Jin Hao escape from her to avoid a misunderstanding, but Jian Hong spots them. Jian Hong is heartbroken and she decides to bring forward the day she starts working as a dance hostess. Hui Min worries for Jian Hong, so Jian Hong reassures Hui Min she will never become a prostitute. Xiao Bei returns home after a profitable night of business, only to hear De Hua has proposed to Jian Hong. De Hua offers to help settle Yao Shi's debts if Jian Hong marries him. Though it is no small sum, De Hua reveals he has other sources of ‘income'. Jian Hong refuses to let De Hua take the risk for her, so she rejects his proposal. She also discloses she likes Xiao Bei, but as soon as De Hua leaves, Jian Hong tells Xiao Bei she is only using him as an excuse...

Wu Ji approaches “Big Black Mole”, who suggests that Wu Ji works as a transvestite on Bugis Street. Wu Ji accepts, and he practises walking with high heels shoes. When Jin Hao walks in on him, Wu Ji confides in her. It breaks Xiao Bei and Tarzan's heart when Lucy teaches Jian Hong how to dance, yet Jian Hong has trouble trying to dance alluringly. Xiao Bei tries to help Jian Hong. He asks Jin Hao to chip in for the capital to sell a batch of fashionable new bras. To help with the business, Jin Hao volunteers to model for Xiao Bei, so he can take some product photographs. When Jin Hao learns that Xiao Bei is raising money for Jian Hong, Jin Hao asks Xiao Bei if he would do the same for her. Jin Hao is elated Xiao Bei says yes. He Jiao returns. Xiao Bei and Jin Hao escape from her to avoid a misunderstanding, but Jian Hong spots them. Jian Hong is heartbroken and she decides to bring forward the day she starts working as a dance hostess. Hui Min worries for Jian Hong, so Jian Hong reassures Hui Min she will never become a prostitute. Mao Mao and Xiang Lin treat Lucy and Inspector Yang to a lavish ‘bird's nest in chicken' meal. When Hui Min discovers that the police are accepting bribes openly, she wants her parents to file a report, yet her parents hesitate as Inspector Yang has a hold on them. Inspector Yang wants Lucy to find him an innocent-looking beauty so he can make his new superior cooperate with him. Lucy thinks of Jian Hong. Yao Shi asks Jian Hong why she turns De Hua down. She explains she cannot let De Hua shoulder their debt. Neither will she use her marriage as repayment for his debt. Tarzan also tries to help Jian Hong, but his meagre salary forbids him to do so. He lies to He Jiao he needs money for English lessons, but the sum is still too little. Everyone is discussing an urban legend that eating pork will give men genital retraction, so Tarzan pretends he needs treatment from Yao Shi and demands $7,000 from Li Fa and He Jiao. Unfortunately, his plan fails and he gets a beating instead...

Xiao Bei gives Yao Shi some money and suggests that Yao Shi arrange to repay his debtors by instalments. Yao Shi is about to accept, but Jian Hong rejects Xiao Bei's money. To stop Xiao Bei and Tarzan from coming up with more ideas, she breaks off her friendship with them. “Big Black Mole” sends his men to take Wu Ji to Bugis Street. The driver of the unlicensed taxi recognises Wu Ji and informs Yao Shi, but Yao Shi refuses to believe him. Wu Ji runs away when a foreigner starts groping him. He runs into Hui Min, and she helps him avoid the men of “Big Black Mole”. Just as Wu Ji thinks he is safe, he bumps into Yao Shi. Yao Shi blows his top. Hui Min gets into trouble with the men of “Big Black Mole” because of Wu Ji. A Caucasian man stops the gangsters from bullying Hui Min, and he introduces himself as Jack, an American soldier stationed in Vietnam. Yao Shi beats Wu Ji up. Jin Hao informs Jian Hong, but when Jian Hong returns home, Wu Ji is already unconscious. Jin Hao manages to find an empty unlicensed taxi to take Wu Ji to the hospital, but its driver is nowhere to be found. Tarzan volunteers to drive Wu Ji, but they nearly meet with an accident. Fortunately, they meet Xiao Bei on the way and he saves the day. Xiao Bei and Tarzan yell at Yao Shi as they explain why Wu Ji works as a transvestite. Feeling remorse, Yao Shi asks the two lads to beat him up. Though Xiao Bei and Tarzan helped Jian Hong, she insists they are no longer friends. Meanwhile, Tarzan gives up his dream of becoming a car racer. Xiang Lin brings home a television set, with the intention of organising ‘tikam' gambling. Hui Min advises him to drop the idea, as the government is clamping down on ‘tikam', but Xiang Lin refuses to listen to her. Tarzan becomes interested in wrestling after watching it on television. When he learns a wrestler nicknamed “Tiger King” is accepting students, he enrols for his classes. Hui Min meets Jack again, and she shows him the way to a church. Xiang Lin and Mao Mao get worried, so Xiao Bei decides to follow Hui Min to take a look. Xiao Bei sees Jack touching Hui Min, so he pushes Jack away. Jack gets angry, so they get into a scuffle…

Jin Hao makes Xiao Bei audition with her at a recording company, yet she blames Xiao Bei for quashing her dream of becoming a singer. Xiao Bei advises her to face up to the reality that she cannot sing. Just as Jin Hao is about to leave in disappointment, they are given another chance to audition again. Hui Min understands Jian Hong breaks her friendship with Xiao Bei and Tarzan for their own good. While Jian Hong knows the others will look down on her, she believes she can keep her self-respect as long as she doesn't prostitute herself. After asking around, Xiao Bei discovers the sort of humiliation dance hostesses have to tolerate. As he fears Jian Hong cannot adjust to that kind of environment, he takes Jian Hong out drinking and provokes her with harsh words. Tarzan gets angry and he wants to hit Xiao Bei. Xiang Lin uses attractive prizes as draw for his ‘tikam' business, but he rigs the spinning wheel so that it is impossible to win. When everyone has their eyes on the big prizes, all Tarzan wants is a small bracelet. Xiang Lin lies that the bracelet has been blessed by a powerful monk, so Tarzan plans to give it to Jian Hong. On seeing Tarzan spends a lot of money on betting, Xiang Lin gives Tarzan a chance. Jian Hong accepts the bracelet with gratitude. On the night Jian Hong is starting work, she feels a chill in her heart because Xiao Bei seems unconcerned. However, just as Jian Hong is about to get into her ride, Xiao Bei shouts from upstairs that he loves her. He also lights some firecrackers to send her off, attracting many sideward glances from the neighbours.

A year passed. Xiao Bei and Wu Ji become members of the People's Defence Force; Jin Hao has signed with a recording company; Tarzan does well in learning wrestling; and Hui Min gets into university… Hui Min gets interviewed for topping the general examination. While He Jiao tries to share Hui Min's limelight, Wu Ji blames Yao Shi for causing him to drop out from school. Yao Shi's gambling habit has also gone from bad to worse, so Wu Ji worries there will be no end to Jian Hong's plight. Tarzan teaches Yao Shi a lesson with his wrestling skills. Xiao Bei praises his proficiency in wrestling, so Tarzan sets his mind on becoming a wrestler. Every night, Xiao Bei waits for Jian Hong outside the nightclub to protect her. Although Jian Hong refuses to entertain her customers beyond accompanying them to dance, Lucy wants her to entertain Yu Ming. Yu Ming is Inspector Yang's superior, and Inspector Yang is secretly trying to get rid of him by using Jian Hong. When Jin Hao asks when she can release an album, Manager Niu hints for her to make some sacrifices. Jin Hao agrees to accompany Manager Niu on his business trip to Kuala Lumpur. When Wu Ji discovers, he follows them secretly. Jian Hong searches for Wu Ji as he is missing. She has been keeping a low profile since she became a dance hostess, yet Xiao Bei insists on making their friendship known and follows her day-in and day-out. Jian Hong is bemused by his behaviour. Despite giving Xiao Bei the cold shoulder, Jian Hong still cares for him. When she discovers “Big Black Mole” is out to get Xiao Bei, Jian Hong helps Xiao Bei. Hui Min advises Jian Hong not to hide her feelings for Xiao Bei anymore, but Jian Hong feels inferior. Hui Min has a bad cough for a long time. As there are rumours of a Hong Kong Flu epidemic, Xiang Lin and Mao Mao worry for Hui Min. Jin Hao and Manager Niu arrive in Kuala Lumpur. When Manager Niu comes knocking on her hotel room door, Jin Hao hesitates...

Hui Min advises Jian Hong not to hide her feelings for Xiao Bei anymore, but Jian Hong feels inferior. Hui Min has a bad cough for a long time. As there are rumours of a Hong Kong Flu epidemic, Xiang Lin and Mao Mao worry for Hui Min. Jin Hao and Manager Niu arrive in Kuala Lumpur. When Manager Niu comes knocking on her hotel room door, Jin Hao hesitates...

Jin Hao refuses Manager Niu, but he spikes her drink. Fortunately, Wu Ji shows up in time. Though Jin Hao escapes rape, she is sad she lost her chance of becoming a singer. As Hui Min fails to recover from her bad cough, He Jiao seizes the chance to spread rumours about her health, so as to instigate the other tenants to force her family to move out. Xiang Lin and Mao Mao refuse to move, so He Jiao snitch on Mao Mao's illegal betting business. Yu Ming arrests Xiang Lin and Mao Mao, but he hopes they can help expose the corrupted cops within the force. As Inspector Yang warns the couple beforehand, they kept their silence. He Jiao evicts Hui Min by force. Jian Hong points out that the doctor confirms Hui Min does not have the Hong Kong flu, but He Jiao insists. When Xiao Bei returns, he sends Hui Min back to her room. He Jiao and Li Fa try to stop him, but with the help of Tarzan, Jin Hao and Jian Hong, Xiao Bei manages to stop He Jiao from chasing Hui Min out.

Jian Hong and Xiao Bei take turns to take care of Hui Min, as they fear He Jiao will try to evict Hui Min again. In appreciation, Hui Min wants Jian Hong to be her god-sister. Jian Hong refuses as she feels inferior. Yu Ming is attracted to Jian Hong, so Inspector Yang and Lucy are secretly pleased. When Yu Ming discovers why Jian Hong became a dance hostess, he reveals his father is also a gambler. That is why he tries hard to clamp down gambling. Jian Hong feels he is a good police officer. Xiao Bei scares away a customer that tries to drag Jian Hong to a hotel. Jian Hong knows Xiao Bei is protecting her secretly, so she is filled with gratitude. Li Fa docks Tarzan's pay for accepting a counterfeit $50 note. Tired of working in the coffee shop, Tarzan tries to enter a Southeast Asian wrestling competition by approaching a professional manager. The manager dissuades him, while another wrestler makes a fool out of Tarzan to please his lady companion. Tarzan vows revenge. Xiao Bei gets disqualified from a man hunt contest, but it inspires him to organise his own competitions. He convinces the person in charge of an expo to let him organise a “Miss Swimwear” contest. Jian Hong feels perturbed by Yao Shi's gambling habit, so Xiao Bei suggests hypnotism. Jian Hong refutes him. Yao Shi chalks up another huge gambling debt. Jian Hong begs Yao Shi to give her a break, so Yao Shi smashes his hands with a rock out of shame. Xiao Bei and Tarzan continue to fight for Jian Hong's heart. Xiao Bei makes a bet with Tarzan to see who can ask Jian Hong out for a movie on her birthday. Tarzan agrees, and he gets someone to write a love poem for him to please Jian Hong...

Tarzan spots the guy that gave him the counterfeit note. Though the guy escape, he leaves behind a lot of counterfeit notes. Tarzan thinks of using the counterfeit notes to settle Yao Shi's debt. As “Big Black Mole” read about the counterfeit notes in the news, Tarzan gets a beating instead. Xiao Bei saves Tarzan, but Tarzan is seriously injured. At the hospital, Tarzan tells Xiao Bei he concedes defeat, but Xiao Bei lectures him about giving up Jian Hong so easily. Tarzan asks Jian Hong for a date. To his surprise, she accepts. Xiao Bei ‘borrows' a customer's suit for his pageant press conference, and Lin Yi panics when he discovers the suit missing. Hui Min worries Xiao Bei will get into more trouble, but he is confident he will succeed. Jin Hao enters the pageant and she wants Wu Ji to give her a swimsuit. Wu Ji uses the rent money for his comic book stall to buy Jin Hao one, so Jian Hong thinks he is irresponsible. When Wu Ji retorts he is tired of being penniless due to Yao Shi's gambling habit, Jian Hong is speechless. Inspector Yang and Lucy want Jian Hong to get Yu Ming drunk, so they can report him to the anti-corruption bureau and have Yu Ming fired. Jian Hong obeys, but Xiao Bei is mistaken Yu Ming wants to rape Jian Hong. With no time to explain, Jian Hong slaps Xiao Bei. After Xiao Bei leaves, she wakes Yu Ming up and asks him to leave. Jian Hong gets worried when Xiao Bei fails to return home that night. When he returns, he ignores Jian Hong, and claims he will have nothing to do with her from then on...

Hui Min senses something is wrong between Jian Hong and Xiao Bei. Instead of telling Hui Min what happened, Xiao Bei asks for her help. To get his pageant in the news, Xiao Bei needs to let the reporter photograph someone in swimsuit. He is surprised Hui Min agrees, while Jin Hao seizes the chance as her opportunity in becoming famous. Though Tarzan wins his bet with Xiao Bei, he discovers Jian Hong agrees only out of gratitude. Tarzan wants another bet because he believes Xiao Bei loses to him deliberately, but Xiao Bei advises Tarzan to be more practical, as Jian Hong may already have other suitors. Jian Hong worries Inspector Yang and Lucy will hold a grudge against her because she let Yu Ming go, yet Lucy offers to help Jian Hong settle her father's debt. In reality, Lucy is plotting her revenge. Jin Hao is furious the article featured only Hui Min, while He Jiao stirs trouble by telling Mao Mao that Xiao Bei made use of Hui Min. Mao Mao and Xiang Lin confront Lin Yi and A Wei, so Lin Yi reprimands Xiao Bei. His scolding falls onto deaf ears, as Xiao Bei is elated he gets publicity for his pageant. Hui Min speaks up for Xiao Bei, and her speech about women's liberation shocks everyone. Yu Ming visits Jian Hong to thank her. Tarzan misunderstands Yu Ming is harassing Jian Hong, but Xiao Bei stops him from attacking Yu Ming. As Tarzan argues with Xiao Bei, Jian Hong reveals Xiao Bei is mistaken about her and Yu Ming. Tarzan reprimands Xiao Bei for not believing in Jian Hong. Xiao Bei slaps himself in guilt after he finds out the truth from Yu Ming. With his cheeks swollen, Xiao Bei asks Jian Hong to forgive him.

He Jiao arranges a matchmaking session for Jin Hao, so Wu Ji gets worried. Jin Hao asks Wu Ji to help sabotage the session, but it is Xiao Bei who takes Jin Hao away from it instead. He Jiao is furious and she demands compensation from Lin Yi and A Wei. Xiao Bei plans to stage a ‘Mermaid A-go-go' performance during the pageant. Jin Hao claims she is an A-go-go expert, but when Xiao Bei asks her to teach the ‘mermaid', she fails to deliver. Jian Hong offers her help. As He Jiao insists that Lin Yi compensates her, Lin Yi blames Xiao Bei for being a troublemaker. Xiao Bei decides to move out to pursue his dreams, so he entrusts his parents into Jian Hong's care. Jian Hong agrees. Tarzan wants to follow Xiao Bei. Though Xiao Bei turns him down, Tarzan is determined. He Jiao fears Jin Hao will leave with the guys, so she refuses to let Jin Hao step out of the house. On the night of the pageant, Jin Hao asks Hui Min for help, and Hui Min manages to get her there on time. Xiao Bei asks Hui Min to stand in as master-of-ceremony because his show host fails to turn up. Convinced that Xiao Bei is going to make her the winner, Jin Hao is about to accept her crown...

To Jin Hao's surprise, someone else is made champion. Jin Hao feels Xiao Bei betrayed her. The pageant is a huge success and Xiao Bei gives everyone a treat, but Jin Hao is still displeased. Tarzan chides Jin Hao, but Jin Hao insists Xiao Bei must have accepted bribe. Xiao Bei admits and he promises to make up to Jin Hao, yet Jin Hao leaves without taking his money. Xiao Bei gives Tarzan $800 for his cut in the profit, but reveals he kept $12,000. When Xiao Bei explains he plan to use it to redeem Jian Hong, Tarzan returns his share to Xiao Bei as well. Jin Hao is upset Xiao Bei betrayed her. Wu Ji comforts her, so Jin Hao treats him to a piece of cake. When He Jiao walks in, Wu Ji returns the cake cowardly, and Jin Hao is furious with Wu Ji's timidity. Regretting his reaction, Wu Ji asks Jin Hao to give him a treat again. This time, he eats the cake and ignores He Jiao's screaming. Wu Ji tells Jian Hong he wants to look for a job as he no longer wants to be a useless bum. Jian Hong is elated. After a short hiatus, Yao Shi starts gambling again. Jian Hong asks Yu Ming for help, so he raids the gambling den and gives Yao Shi a warning. He even spot checks on Yao Shi, so Jian Hong is grateful. With the anti-corruption bureau close on his back, Inspector Yang decides to sacrifice De Hua. Inspector Yang promises to reward De Hua after his release from jail, but De Hua has other plans. Xiao Bei and Tarzan give Jian Hong the sum, and they swear they earned it through proper means. Jian Hong is touched. Lucy congratulates Jian Hong, but she secretly sold Jian Hong to a customer. Though Xiao Bei arrives in time to take Jian Hong away, Inspector Yang stops Xiao Bei with his pistol. Just then, De Hua arrives...

To Jin Hao's surprise, someone else is made champion. Jin Hao feels Xiao Bei betrayed her. The pageant is a huge success and Xiao Bei gives everyone a treat, but Jin Hao is still displeased. Tarzan chides Jin Hao, but Jin Hao insists Xiao Bei must have accepted bribe. Xiao Bei admits and he promises to make up to Jin Hao, yet Jin Hao leaves without taking his money. Xiao Bei gives Tarzan $800 for his cut in the profit, but reveals he kept $12,000. When Xiao Bei explains he plan to use it to redeem Jian Hong, Tarzan returns his share to Xiao Bei as well. Jin Hao is upset Xiao Bei betrayed her. Wu Ji comforts her, so Jin Hao treats him to a piece of cake. When He Jiao walks in, Wu Ji returns the cake cowardly, and Jin Hao is furious with Wu Ji's timidity. Regretting his reaction, Wu Ji asks Jin Hao to give him a treat again. This time, he eats the cake and ignores He Jiao's screaming. Wu Ji tells Jian Hong he wants to look for a job as he no longer wants to be a useless bum. Jian Hong is elated. Jian Hong finally quits, and she makes a living by selling household items. Wu Ji finds a job in a finance company; Xiao Bei makes a lot of money by organising various types of contests; and Tarzan fulfils his wish of becoming a wrestler. A rich young man hires Jin Hao as his secretary, but all she needs to do is to accompany him gallivanting every day. One day, he makes Jin Hao dress up as Marilyn Monroe. Jin Hao introduces her boss to Xiao Bei and suggests Xiao Bei help organise a ‘search for Marilyn Monroe' contest. Xiao Bei warns Jin Hao about the guy. Sure enough, the guy tries to rape Jin Hao. Fortunately, Xiao Bei and Tarzan rescue Jin Hao. Xiao Bei spends his money as fast as he earns it, and he is extremely generous with Jin Hao. When Jin Hao gets drunk and insists he says that he loves her, Xiao Bei obliges. He Jiao changes her attitude towards Xiao Bei as he is now rich, so she tries to marry Jin Hao to Xiao Bei. When Li Fa reminds her that Xiao Bei loves Jian Hong, she visits Lin Yi and A Wei to malign Jian Hong of using ‘gong-tau' black magic on Xiao Bei. A Wei believes He Jiao. Lin Yi, on the other hand, is filled with gratitude towards Jian Hong. He advises A Wei not to be fooled by the mediums, but A Wei refuses to listen to him. Jian Hong is sad A Wei is wary of her. Although Jian Hong is no longer a dance hostess, everyone looks down on her. Even when Mao Mao sees Hui Min practising how to dance, she is convinced Jian Hong leads Hui Min astray. Tarzan makes a name for himself in the wrestling circle as the “Tiger King”. He wishes to let Jian Hong watch him wrestle, so he ignores Xiao Bei's objection and invites her to one of his matches. Jian Hong worries for Tarzan during his fight, while Tarzan plans to express his love for her...

Jian Hong asks Xiao Bei to stop the match, but Xiao Bei points out that wrestling gets exciting only when blood spills. Tarzan turns around to win the match. Jian Hong advises Tarzan to quit being a wrestler, but Tarzan insists, as this is the only area he can do better than Xiao Bei. He vows to outdo Xiao Bei and marry Jian Hong. When he professes his love, Jian Hong is at a loss what she should do. Xiao Bei and Tarzan return home with a lot of expensive electrical appliances, and He Jiao warms up to Xiao Bei. Lin Yi and A Wei are pleased with Xiao Bei's success, but A Wei warns Xiao Bei to be wary of the ‘fox spirit'. When Xiao Bei realises A Wei refers to Jian Hong, he rebukes her. Xiao Bei wants to take Jian Hong to a hotel for high tea. He also gives Jian Hong some money, but Jin Hao shouts “Xiao Bei Darling” from upstairs. Although Xiao Bei explains that Jin Hao forced him, Jian Hong is displeased Xiao Bei pushes all the blame on Jin Hao. Xiao Bei consults Hui Min, who advises Xiao Bei to marry Jian Hong soon. De Hua proposes to Jian Hong again suddenly. Yao Shi advises Jian Hong to accept, but she objects. Yao Shi asks Jian Hong to forget Xiao Bei, as A Wei has been speaking ill of her. De Hua warns Xiao Bei to stay away from Jian Hong or he will ‘take care' of him. When Xiao Bei rebukes him, he gives Xiao Bei a sinister look. Xiao Bei decides to propose to Jian Hong with Tarzan and Hui Min as witness. Jian Hong accepts, and Tarzan is heartbroken. A Wei passes out on hearing that Xiao Bei insists on marrying Jian Hong, while Jin Hao gets drunk. Wu Ji feels worried...

Jian Hong ponders if she should elope with Xiao Bei. When she finally decides to heed Hui Min's advice and is about to start packing, Wu Ji tells her that Jin Hao is getting herself drunk. She hurries to stop Jin Hao. “Big Black Mole” instigates Jin Hao to injure Jian Hong. When Xiao Bei arrives, he takes Jian Hong to a hospital. Although Xiao Bei suspects Jin Hao, Wu Ji claims “Big Black Mole” is responsible. Xiao Bei tries to seek revenge, but “Big Black Mole” is armed. After Xiao Bei leaves, De Hua appears and he kills “Big Black Mole”. De Hua frames Xiao Bei for the murder. Although Xiao Bei claims innocence, De Hua persuades him to plead guilty. Xiao Bei refuses. Hui Min hires a lawyer for Xiao Bei and she tries to find some witnesses. When Mao Mao and Xiang Lin try to stop her, Hui Min rebukes them by saying she cannot be ungrateful towards Xiao Bei and Jian Hong. Hui Min locates a crucial witness, but the witness feigns ignorance. Jian Hong disregards her injury to beg the witness, so the witness finally agrees to testify. Yu Ming is now an anti-corruption investigation officer and he is following a lead through “Big Black Mole”. He discovers De Hua may be involved in the death of “Big Black Mole”, but De Hua escapes. After Xiao Bei gets his name cleared, he hugs Jian Hong...

Heartbroken, Jin Hao falls sick. He Jiao seeks help from a Taoist priest. Yao Shi finally agrees to let Xiao Bei and Jian Hong be together, but Jian Hong stops Xiao Bei from telling his parents as A Wei is still unwell. Wu Ji is worried Jin Hao fails to get better. In her daze, Jin Hao mistakes Wu Ji for Xiao Bei and she holds on to him tightly. Wu Ji panics as he will be late for work. Wu Ji's manager Yan Xia, who is also his boss' spinster daughter, likes Wu Ji. She intends to let Wu Ji handle the distribution of the employees' salaries, and she hints at promoting Wu Ji. The Taoist priest instructs He Jiao to keep watch while he ‘treats' Jin Hao in her room alone. Xiao Bei advises He Jiao to open the door but she refuses. Wu Ji breaks in and rescues Jin Hao from being raped. When Jin Hao recovers, she changes her attitude towards Wu Ji. Wu Ji is elated. Tarzan tailors a pair of bell-bottomed pants and Lin Yi cannot understand how this strange-looking pair of pants can get so popular. A thug comes collecting protection money in a Bruce Lee outfit, and Tarzan wants to teach him a lesson for insulting his idol. Jian Hong wants Xiao Bei to stop him, but Xiao Bei eggs Tarzan on instead. Concerned about Xiao Bei's uninhibited nature, Jian Hong advises Tarzan not to obey Xiao Bei all the time. Tarzan is facing “Mountain Wolf” in a duel soon, and “Mountain Wolf” secretly vows to end Tarzan's wrestling career. Despite Xiao Bei's assurance that “Mountain Wolf” will comply with the organiser's results arrangement, Tarzan continues to practise hard. Jian Hong worries for Tarzan's safety, so she advises Xiao Bei to call the match off. Xiao Bei reassures her that the match is staged and there will be no real danger, but Jian Hong still feels uneasy. Jin Hao makes Xiao Bei treat her to a steak meal. When she is done, she tells Xiao Bei she will no longer harass him, and asks that he loves Jian Hong devotedly. Xiao Bei is stunned.

Wu Ji breaks in and rescues Jin Hao from being raped. When Jin Hao recovers, she changes her attitude towards Wu Ji. Wu Ji is elated. Tarzan tailors a pair of bell-bottomed pants and Lin Yi cannot understand how this strange-looking pair of pants can get so popular. A thug comes collecting protection money in a Bruce Lee outfit, and Tarzan wants to teach him a lesson for insulting his idol. Jian Hong wants Xiao Bei to stop him, but Xiao Bei eggs Tarzan on instead. Concerned about Xiao Bei's uninhibited nature, Jian Hong advises Tarzan not to obey Xiao Bei all the time. Tarzan is facing “Mountain Wolf” in a duel soon, and “Mountain Wolf” secretly vows to end Tarzan's wrestling career. Despite Xiao Bei's assurance that “Mountain Wolf” will comply with the organiser's results arrangement, Tarzan continues to practise hard. Jian Hong worries for Tarzan's safety, so she advises Xiao Bei to call the match off. Xiao Bei reassures her that the match is staged and there will be no real danger, but Jian Hong still feels uneasy. Jin Hao makes Xiao Bei treat her to a steak meal. When she is done, she tells Xiao Bei she will no longer harass him, and asks that he loves Jian Hong devotedly. Xiao Bei is stunned.

Heartbroken, Jin Hao falls sick. He Jiao seeks help from a Taoist priest. Yao Shi finally agrees to let Xiao Bei and Jian Hong be together, but Jian Hong stops Xiao Bei from telling his parents as A Wei is still unwell. Wu Ji is worried Jin Hao fails to get better. In her daze, Jin Hao mistakes Wu Ji for Xiao Bei and she holds on to him tightly. Wu Ji panics as he will be late for work. He Jiao gets a matchmaker to find Tarzan a wife. Tarzan resists at first, until he meets Jin Zhu. Xiao Bei sponsors Tarzan to have his first date with Jin Zhu, and love blossoms between Tarzan and Jin Zhu. At the match, “Mountain Wolf” resorts to dirty tricks and hurts Tarzan's groin. Xiao Bei ambushes “Mountain Wolf” but gets beaten up instead. When Xiao Bei arrives at the hospital, he discovers Tarzan may be incapable of having children. The neighbours stop He Jiao from attacking Xiao Bei. Lin Yi and A Wei think He Jiao is too harsh on their son, yet Xiao Bei apologises. He Jiao wants him to take full responsibility. On discovering Tarzan's condition, Xiang Lin plans to get back at He Jiao by conning her. He pretends he knows a miracle doctor, so He Jiao begs him for help. Xiao Bei turns into a recluse. He asks Jian Hong to give all his money to Tarzan, but avoids visiting Tarzan personally. After his surgery, Tarzan becomes extremely sensitive and violent. Jian Hong feels sad. Jian Hong counsels Tarzan, but Tarzan asks for Xiao Bei. Jian Hong explains Xiao Bei's condition and she gives Tarzan the money. Though Tarzan refuses to accept, He Jiao pockets it and refuses to give it back.

Tarzan wants Jian Hong to tell Xiao Bei he does not blame him, but Xiao Bei continues to mope around. Jian Hong asks Hui Min for help. Hui Min points out that only Jian Hong can help Xiao Bei, as she is the most important person in his heart! Jin Hao starts working as a perfume salesgirl and she agrees to have lunch with Wu Ji one day. After she talks to restaurant owner Zheng Dong, she gets close to Wu Ji and asks if he can smell Zheng Dong's body odour on her. Wu Ji gets excited. Yao Shi wants Jian Hong to ditch Xiao Bei and marry roast meat shop owner “Pig Skull”. Jian Hong ignores him. He then wants to find Wu Ji a wife, but Wu Ji knows he wants only Jin Hao. Wu Ji accompanies Yan Xia shopping and she is upset when Wu Ji gets chummy with Jin Hao. After Wu Ji saves Yan Xia from an armed robber, Yan Xia treats him differently, and rumours spread within the office that Yan Xia is interested in Wu Ji. Wu Ji ignores the rumours at first, until his boss invites him for dinner. Yao Shi asks Lin Yi to tailor Wu Ji a new suit for the dinner, while Wu Ji is both happy and worried. He is happy he has hopes for a promotion, but worried what he should do if Yan Xia is really interested in him. Zheng Dong takes Jin Hao out for a meal and he invites her to model for his mooncake products. After starving for three days, Xiao Bei gorges himself suddenly. Jian Hong and Jin Hao try to stop him from self-destruction, but Xiao Bei refuses to listen...

Not even Jian Hong can persuade Xiao Bei to liven up, so Tarzan asks Jian Hong to take Xiao Bei to him. Xiao Bei accidentally discovers the miracle doctor is in cahoots with Xiang Lin, and Tarzan has no hope of recovering. His sense of guilt deepens. Yao Shi publicises around that Wu Ji is invited to dinner with his big boss. This is the first time Wu Ji feels he can make Yao Shi proud. Feeling encouraged, Wu Ji asks Jin Hao out for a movie, and Jin Hao accepts. The boss likes Wu Ji, and Wu Ji gets a promotion after agreeing to date Yan Xia. Jin Hao, who is clueless Wu Ji has chosen his career over her, feels happy for him. Zheng Dong tells Jin Hao he likes her. Though Jin Hao has no feelings for him, she hesitates on thinking she can become a rich tai-tai after marrying him. Jian Hong stops A Wei from pampering Xiao Bei with lots of food, yet A Wei hits her with a spatula. Jian Hong asks Lin Yi for help, but even a beating fails to rouse Xiao Bei. Jian Hong drags Xiao Bei to Tarzan and Tarzan gives him a good scolding. As Xiao Bei continues to mope around, Hui Min thinks of a plan and they make Xiao Bei agree to become a fishmonger. Jin Zhu's parents reject the marriage proposal as they heard about Tarzan's injury, so He Jiao offers a higher dowry...

Jin Zhu's parents reject the marriage proposal as they heard about Tarzan's injury, so He Jiao offers a higher dowry...

Tarzan gets discharged and He Jiao agrees to give Jin Zhu's parents $6,000 as dowry. Tarzan overhears Jin Zhu telling her mother she is willing to marry Tarzan regardless of the rumours. Although he feels touched, he decides not to sacrifice Jin Zhu's happiness on second thought. Tarzan asks Xiao Bei to leave home with him again, and he pays a prostitute to convince Xiao Bei he is well. Unfortunately, Xiao Bei sees through his ploy. When the “miracle doctor” tries to cheat He Jiao again, Tarzan exposes his tricks and beats him up. Tarzan tells He Jiao he refuses to marry Jin Zhu. Later that night when he is alone, Tarzan cries as he truly loves Jin Zhu. When Xiao Bei fails to show up on the day Tarzan plans to go away, Tarzan leaves alone. Tarzan wants revenge. He discovers “Mountain Wolf”, scorned by the wrestling world, is now participating in underground matches. Tarzan joins in so he can meet “Mountain Wolf” in the rink again. Xiao Bei tells Jian Hong he has no intention of selling fish or helping Jian Hong at her stall. He decides to become a tailor, but is really bad at it. Jian Hong encourages Xiao Bei not to give up on himself, yet Xiao Bei wants a break-up. Disappointed, Jian Hong returns Xiao Bei his ring and she agrees to marry “Pig Skull”. When Jin Hao is taking stock in the storeroom, she has no idea there is a fire in the departmental store...

When Jin Hao is taking stock in the storeroom, she has no idea there is a fire in the departmental store...

Wu Ji dashes in to save Jin Hao, but both of them get trapped. Touched by Wu Ji's sincerity, Jin Hao promises to marry Wu Ji if they survive the fire. The fire fighters save them, so Jin Hao intends to tell their parents about her relationship with Wu Ji. Wu Ji plans to reject Yan Xia, but later decides to give Jin Hao up instead. Jin Hao is deeply hurt when Wu Ji denies their wedding plans in front of their parents. Xiao Bei asks “Pig Skull” to give up on marrying Jian Hong, but “Pig Skull” refuses. When he fails to dissuade Jian Hong, Xiao Bei seeks help from Hui Min. Hui Min try to help the couple patch up secretly. Xiang Lin runs away with Mao Mao's money. He plans to cohabit with his young new lover, but gets conned instead. Now penniless, he tries to ask his neighbour for a bowl of noodles, but another neighbour informs Mao Mao. Mao Mao tries to torch Xiang Lin down, so Xiang Lin advises Xiao Bei not to end up like him. Xiao Bei gets enlightened! When Yao Shi dresses up to meet with his would be in-laws, the neighbours discover Wu Ji is marrying his boss' daughter. He Jiao plans to get back at Wu Ji by splashing him with human waste…

Jin Hao stops He Jiao. Wu Ji feels guilty, yet Yao Shi is elated both his children are getting married. On the day “Pig Skull” is presenting Jian Hong his betrothal gifts, Jian Hong quietly awaits her fate. Xiao Bei intercepts “Pig Skull”, and “Pig Skull” beats Xiao Bei up. Jian Hong realises something is amiss. When she arrives, Xiao Bei is badly beaten up, yet he refuses to let “Pig Skull” get past. On seeing Jian Hong still loves Xiao Bei, “Pig Skull” gives Xiao Bei the betrothal gifts. Xiao Bei and Jian Hong tell Lin Yi and A Wei they wish to get married. Although A Wei objects, Lin Yi convinces her. Tarzan watches on sadly as Xiao Bei and Jian Hong prepare to get married, while “Mountain Wolf” accepts Tarzan's challenge. “Japanese Guy” informs Xiao Bei as he is afraid “Mountain Wolf” will plot against Tarzan, but Tarzan refuses to listen to Xiao Bei. Although “Mountain Wolf” resorts to dirty tricks, he is no match for Tarzan. Tarzan is about to make “Mountain Wolf” suffer his same fate, but later decides to spare the guy. Wu Ji shows Yao Shi his new house. All of a sudden, Yan Xia accuses Wu Ji of keeping his family background from her. She threatens to call off their wedding and fire Wu Ji, so Wu Ji begs Yan Xia. Yan Xia wants him to relinquish his ties with his family, and she will not let Yao Shi and Jian Hong attend their wedding, nor offer tea to Yao Shi. Wu Ji agrees. When Yao Shi objects, Wu Ji says he brings this to himself. Despite Xiao Bei's warning, Jin Hao attends an audition and is offered a movie contract in Hong Kong. Jin Hao tries to leave secretly, but Xiao Bei and Tarzan stop her. He Jiao locks Jin Hao in her room...

Jian Hong advises Wu Ji to stand up to Yan Xia, for the least she can do is offer tea to Yao Shi on their wedding day. Wu Ji keeps quiet as Yan Xia promotes him and gives him car and chauffeur benefits. Jin Hao begs Wu Ji, so he helps her escape. He Jiao is furious and Jian Hong has to stop her from entering their room. Yao Shi scolds Wu Ji, for he can avoid He Jiao after he moves away, but Yao Shi and Jian Hong have to face her every day. When Wu Ji promises to help them move, Yao Shi mocks at his son. Yao Shi is frustrated, yet he has to put up a happy front when the neighbours congratulate him. He decides he must let Yan Xia offer him tea at all costs. On Wu Ji's wedding day, He Jiao tries to splash him with human waste, but Xiang Lin bumps right into her. No matter how Mao Mao treats him, Xiang Lin refuses to leave or divorce Mao Mao. Jian Hong gets worried when Yao Shi dresses up and claims he is going to accept tea offering from his daughter-in-law. Instead of hiding in a hotel as Wu Ji arranged, Yao Shi arrives at Wu Ji's new home. Jian Hong and Xiao Bei try to stop him, and Yan Xia refuses to let them in. Yao Shi coughs out blood in anger… Yao Shi is dying, but Yan Xia refuses to believe Xiao Bei. In anger, Xiao Bei drags them home by force. Yan Xia succumbs to the pressure of the watching crowd, and Yao Shi dies after having his tea.

At Hong Kong, Jin Hao is raped and the human traffickers arrange for her to film pornography. Jin Hao calls home for help, so Xiao Bei and Tarzan bring money to Hong Kong to redeem her. Xiao Bei and Tarzan pay up, but the human traffickers refuse to release Jin Hao. They even plan to sell her to Japan to be a prostitute. Fortunately, Xiao Bei and Tarzan come prepared and they rescue Jin Hao. Xiao Bei asks Tarzan to take Jin Hao away while he distracts the criminals, but he gets shot. Two weeks passed and there is still no news of Xiao Bei. Everyone is convinced he died, but Jian Hong insists he will return home safely, until Lin Yi hires a Taoist priest to summon Xiao Bei's spirit. Jian Hong is pregnant with Xiao Bei's child and she nearly has a miscarriage from grieving too much. As Jian Hong and Xiao Bei are not married, Tarzan suggests that Jian Hong marry him to avoid wagging tongues. Jian Hong accepts.

Jin Hao blames herself for causing Xiao Bei's death. After her ordeal in Hong Kong, Jin Hao gives up on herself and becomes an escort girl. Jian Hong fails to dissuade Jin Hao, while Li Fa feels ashamed of the way Jin Hao dresses. As they often have conflicts, Jin Hao leaves home for good. Jian Hong gives birth to a boy and Tarzan names him Yi Xin. Tarzan insists that Yi Xin calls him uncle, but Jian Hong objects. Tarzan feels grateful. Time flies. Yi Xin is now eight years old. When Yi Xin is playing on the street, Xiao Bei watches him from afar secretly… Yi Xin asks He Jiao if his friends are telling the truth when they say he is not Tarzan's son because Tarzan is a ‘eunuch'. He Jiao tries to stop Yi Xin, but Jian Hong overhears. Jian Hong beats Yi Xin in anger. Fortunately, Hui Min arrives. Yi Xin sends Lin Yi and A Wei some food. The couple has closed their tailor shop and work from home. A Wei cried her eyes blind from missing Xiao Bei, but she thinks Yi Xin resembles Xiao Bei. Lin Yi stops her as it will give Jian Hong trouble. Jian Hong asks Hui Min if she intends to get married, but Hui Min has no feelings for her suitor Louis, who is a doctor. They also reminisce it has been almost 10 years since Xiao Bei died, not knowing he is still alive. Xiao Bei now leads a vagabond life. One night, he thinks back of that fateful day. Xiao Bei survives the shots, but his captors turn him into a junkie and force him to smuggle drugs. In Holland, Xiao Bei runs into De Hua, who is now a drug dealer. The two groups of drug dealers have a conflict, and Xiao Bei kills De Hua. Xiao Bei gets sentenced to ten years jail for drug trafficking and manslaughter... Tarzan partners a friend in managing a tropical fish farm, and he promises to pay for A Wei's eye surgery. Unfortunately, his friend absconds with his money. After being betrayed by friends several times, Tarzan misses Xiao Bei even more.

Instead of scolding Tarzan, Jian Hong encourages Tarzan and promises to help run the fish farm. Jian Hong needs money for the fish farm, but Wu Ji cannot help her because Yan Xia controls his finances. When Jian Hong approaches Jin Hao, Jin Hao gives Jian Hong all her casino winnings without a word. While searching for a witness, Hui Min gets attacked by a junkie. Xiao Bei helps her. Hui Min decides to return and confirm if her rescuer is Xiao Bei. With Louis by her side, she discovers Xiao Bei is now a crippled vagabond. Hui Min is shocked, but Xiao Bei begs her to keep his survival a secret, especially from Jian Hong and Tarzan. Hui Min agrees as she understands his concerns, but she makes Xiao Bei promise never to leave without a word. Xiao Bei moves in with Louis and Hui Min gets him a job in her law firm. Jian Hong and Tarzan work hard, and business at the fish farm begins to pick up. Tarzan breaks his arm by accident, and Jian Hong tires herself out having to take care of the delivery, Yi Xin's schoolwork and also chores for Xiao Bei's parents. When her nose bleeds for no reason, she brushes it off as fatigue. Tarzan appreciates Jian Hong's hard work and he kisses her.
