Jin Hao is now a rich man's mistress, but she squanders her money on gambling. The rich man's wife wants to teach Jin Hao a lesson, but Jin Hao retaliates by splashing kerosene on her attackers and herself. Shocked with her response, the rich man ditches her. Jin Hao loses all her money and she tries to prostitute herself again, but a man claims she has venereal disease. When a doctor confirms her condition, Jin Hao demands compensation from the rich man. The rich man beats her up instead. Jin Hao turns to Wu Ji for help, and he misappropriates company funds to give to Jin Hao. Instead of seeking treatment, Jin Hao gambles the money away. Wu Ji gives Yan Xia some excuse when she asks about the money, but Yan Xia hires someone to check on Wu Ji. Hui Min rekindles her love for Xiao Bei, yet she accepts Louis out of guilt. When He Jiao fails to hear from Jin Hao, Jian Hong visits Jin Hao. She breaks in and discovers Jin Hao is critically ill… Jian Hong admits Jin Hao into a hospital. In her daze, Jin Hao keeps blaming herself for Xiao Bei's death. Jian Hong bumps into Xiao Bei, but brushes it off as her imagination. Hui Min apologises for stopping Jian Hong and Xiao Bei from meeting, yet Xiao Bei claims she did the right thing, as he has no courage to face the others. He hopes Hui Min can let him choose his own path, but Hui Min feels bad for Jian Hong.

Wu Ji gives Yan Xia some excuse when she asks about the money, but Yan Xia hires someone to check on Wu Ji. Hui Min rekindles her love for Xiao Bei, yet she accepts Louis out of guilt. When He Jiao fails to hear from Jin Hao, Jian Hong visits Jin Hao. She breaks in and discovers Jin Hao is critically ill… Jian Hong admits Jin Hao into a hospital. In her daze, Jin Hao keeps blaming herself for Xiao Bei's death. Jian Hong bumps into Xiao Bei, but brushes it off as her imagination. Hui Min apologises for stopping Jian Hong and Xiao Bei from meeting, yet Xiao Bei claims she did the right thing, as he has no courage to face the others. He hopes Hui Min can let him choose his own path, but Hui Min feels bad for Jian Hong.

The rich man's wife wants to teach Jin Hao a lesson, but Jin Hao retaliates by splashing kerosene on her attackers and herself. Shocked with her response, the rich man ditches her. The virus affects Jin Hao's thinking, and she blames Jian Hong and Wu Ji for her predicament. Jian Hong gets dizzy spells but she ignores the signs. Tarzan makes some money in the share market and he buys Jian Hong a ring. Jian Hong cries as it brings back memories of Xiao Bei, and Tarzan realises she still misses Xiao Bei. A Wei claims she saw Xiao Bei, while Yi Xin says he was once saved by someone who resembles Xiao Bei. Jian Hong begins to suspect she did meet Xiao Bei that day, but she soon overturns that thought. Hui Min asks Jian Hong what she would do if Xiao Bei is still alive, since Tarzan is only her husband in name. Jian Hong replies with conviction that nothing can change the experiences they shared as husband and wife. Hui Min feels ashamed of herself. Xiao Bei plans to go sailing. Overcome by her emotions, Hui Min begs Xiao Bei to stay. Xiao Bei rejects her. Jin Hao gets confused and she escapes from the hospital. She asks Wu Ji for money, so Wu Ji suggests she gets someone to ‘rob' him. Yan Xia sees through his tricks, but Jin Hao runs to the rooftop with the money. Claiming she needs it to rescue Xiao Bei, Jin Hao refuses to return the money… Jian Hong, Tarzan and Hui Min try to stop Jin Hao from attempting suicide, yet Jin Hao refuses to step down. Hui Min knows only Xiao Bei can save Jin Hao, so she fetches him there. Everyone is shocked to see Xiao Bei. Jin Hao finally gives up her suicidal thoughts, but she falls backwards from exhaustion. Jian Hong blacks out. When she comes to, she learns that Xiao Bei manages to stop Jin Hao from falling off the building. The doctor discovers Jian Hong has brain tumour and needs surgery. Jian Hong worries she will not wake up after her surgery, so she begs Xiao Bei to stay and help Tarzan. She also apologises to Xiao Bei and reveals that Yi Xin is his son. However, she asks him not to acknowledge Yi Xin. Xiao Bei thanks Jian Hong for taking care of his parents and he promises to stay.

Lin Yi and Ah Wei are elated to see Xiao Bei, while He Jiao worries he will snatch Jian Hong away. Tarzan reprimands his mother. After some drinks, Tarzan tells Xiao Bei he will return Jian Hong to him when she gets well, but Xiao Bei punches him for harbouring such a thought. When Jian Hong sees Tarzan injured, she guesses Xiao Bei must have punched Tarzan for saying the wrong thing. Tarzan admits he is a fool, but Jian Hong claims he is only childlike. Tarzan asks Jian Hong to promise she will wake up from her surgery, and Jian Hong agrees. Jian Hong goes into surgery. Her heart stops during surgery, but her will to live is strong. Though she survives, she slips into a coma, and the doctor says Jian Hong may lose part of or all of her memory. Tarzan takes Yi Xin to the fish farm, so He Jiao asks Yi Xin to keep an eye on Xiao Bei. Yi Xin dislikes Xiao Bei, so Tarzan ill treats Yi Xin, hoping this can bring Yi Xin and Xiao Bei closer. Yi Xin sees through Tarzan's intention, and he writes in his diary Tarzan will always be his best father no matter what. Xiao Bei knows in his heart Yi Xin will never be as close to him as he is to Tarzan… Jian Hong comes to, but she cannot remember Yi Xin or the recent past. On the doctor's advice, everyone decides to let Jian Hong recuperate at the fish farm and not rush her into regaining her memory. Jian Hong remembers the time when Xiao Bei and Tarzan are her best friends, and Tarzan creates opportunities for Jian Hong and Xiao Bei to be alone. Tarzan stops a man from hitting his ex-wife. To his surprise, the woman is Jin Zhu. Tarzan feels apologetic, for he rejected Jin Zhu so she can find happiness, yet she married a violent man who not only hits her, but disfigured her as well.

Xiao Bei wants Tarzan to stop creating opportunities for him and Jian Hong, yet Tarzan persists. Hui Min patches up with Louis. While visiting Jian Hong, she asks Xiao Bei about his future plans, since Jian Hong is gradually regaining her memory. Xiao Bei plans on becoming a sailor, but Hui Min tells him her heartfelt thoughts. She thinks Xiao Bei should stay to give Jian Hong her well-deserved bliss, and believes Tarzan and the others will gradually accept them. Tarzan decides to leave. Jian Hong regains her memory. Yi Xin falls into a pond and Xiao Bei jumps in to save him. However, Xiao Bei gets tangled by some seaweed. Yi Xin shouts for his mother, and Jian Hong rescues Xiao Bei with a bamboo pole. The family finally reunite… It is now the 1990s. Yi Xin is all grown up and a member of the Special Forces in fighting terrorists. The government requisites the old building in North Bridge Road for demolition, so the old neighbours return for a reunion on the last day Li Fa is operating his coffee shop. He Jiao is upset Li Fa's wife and son in China are coming for a visit, so Jian Hong and Jin Hao comfort her. At the reunion, all will be revealed.
